#do a ggplot with it pivot
#pivot wider function 

pre_post%>%
  pivot_longer(., 
               col = c('test1', 'test2'),  
               names_to = 'test',
               values_to = "score"
               ) %>%

  ggplot (data = ., aes (x = test, y = score)) +
  geom_point () +
  geom_smooth ( method = lm)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

#pivot wider function 



 language_diversity %>%
     pivot_wider(
       names_from =  Measurement,
       values_from = Value, 
     ) %>% 
   ggplot (., aes( x = log (Population), y = Langs, label = Country)) +
   geom_point() +
   geom_text () +
   geom_smooth(method = lm)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'
